## Special Cases

### Pull Requests (GitHub / Merge Requests on GitLab)

**Always provide:**
- PR title (concise, under 70 chars)
- PR description/body (markdown formatted)
- Target branch (main, develop, etc.)
- Any review guidelines or merge strategy

**Example:**
```
## Create a Pull Request

Title:
  "feat(blog): implement Drizzle schema + seed + components"

Description:
  "## Changes
  - Migrated blog from static array to Drizzle + Postgres
  - Added 4 new tables with cascade deletes
  - Updated loaders for SSR with published filter
  - Integrated Markdown + media components

  ## Testing
  - [x] typecheck passes
  - [x] build passes
  - [x] /blog and /blog/:slug load correctly
  - [x] draft posts return 404

  Closes #001"

Command:
  gh pr create --title "..." --body "..."
  # OR open GitLab UI and fill form manually
```

### Docker Build & Push

**Always provide step-by-step:**
```
1. Set environment variables in terminal:
   export VITE_SUPABASE_URL="https://..."
   export VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY="pk_..."

2. Login to GitLab Container Registry (one time):
   docker login registry.gitlab.com
   # Use Personal Access Token with 'write_registry' scope

3. Build and push:
   npm run docker:push
   # Or: docker build -t registry.gitlab.com/... . && docker push ...

4. Verify image pushed:
   docker images | grep bizu-hub
```

### Portainer Redeploy

**Provide clear instructions:**
```
1. Open Portainer UI (https://your-vps:9000)
2. Navigate to Stacks → bizu-hub
3. Click "Update the stack"
4. Confirm settings (should pull new image automatically)
5. Check container logs for startup errors
```

---

## When Unsure

If an operation involves **credentials**, **destructive changes**, or **production impact**,
**always ask the user** rather than assume. Frame it as:

> "The next step requires [action].
>
> You can either:
> 1. **I provide instructions** — you execute manually
> 2. **You tell me your preference** — I'll adapt the approach
>
> Which would you prefer?"

